(1)

Kissena Blvd (formerly Jamaica Ave.) at the N.E. corner of Barclay Ave. (formerly Monroe Street), showing the James Varum Graham house in 1926.   It belonged to Mrs. M.E. Corse in 1873.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)

The same showing a more extended view northward.

April 13, 1927.

P.L. Sperr.
